      <p>Notice the inverted yield curve in this example: shorter CDs pay more than longer CDs, which often happens when markets expect future rate cuts. In a normal rate environment, longer CDs would pay more than shorter ones. Use our <a href="/financial-calculators/compound-interest-calculator/">compound interest calculator</a> to model exactly how much you would earn on different deposits at various rates and time periods.</p>
